<h2 id="cr">CREATE statement and datatype explanations</h2>
<i class="no">..after a day of messing with input sctuff..</i>	
<br>	<table>Datatypes
<tr><td>input <td>means.. <td>example <td>means..<td>variations:
<tr><td>varchar<td>varying length of input; alphanumeral; non-unicode; maxiumum input (in parenthesis) is optional<td>varchar(20)<td>varchar, 20 characters in input maximum.<td> char()=fixed length; space placeholders in storage, text=non-standard datatype separate from table objects (see <a href="http://www.pythian.com/blog/text-vs-varchar/">here</a>), 
<tr><td>smallint <td>numeric data, fixed max-value, negative-capable, whole-number only; digits max specified in parenthesis or 32767max<td>smallint(4)<td>smallint, 4 digits in input mx <td>bigint, int=2k million digits max, tinyint=255max, 
<tr><td>float()<td>floating decimal data; unfixed(or specified) number of decimal places.<td>float() 
#later http://beyondrelational.com/quiz/sqlserver/tsql/2011/questions/89/The-misconception-about-FLOAT.aspx
<tr>			
</table>
