<li> Application: SQLite Magic
<li>database created with menu items as .db3 #ed.//#w  
<li> large input of several tables (first FK-referencing the latter) did not work.//
	- #bug! no "copy" function although clicking on the pen-icon, there is "clear", "paste", etc.
	- also could not clear the currently active code "tab" with the above action
	- whilst generally, when the code has not been run at least once, it doesn't bother to save 111
<li>single table ("strawhats") created with single column called "Name"; a primary key.//
<li> foreign key as has been learned at [forgotten or various sources] eg. <i>Name FOREIGN KEY REFERENCES Characters(Name)</i> does not work.//
	- at <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11545189/sqlite-foreign-key">stackoverflow</a>,  <i>FOREIGN KEY(checklist_id) REFERENCES checklist(_id)</i> is found.
	- You need to declare it before you want to set it as FOREIGN KEY. {does not make sense but basically although conflict can arise from things like datatype having already been declared in the mirror primary-key, first declare there is a column as per usual (comman and all) then add the key-link reference thing. seen more prominently at <a href="http://alvinalexander.com/android/sqlite-foreign-keys-example">alivinalexander.com</a> here. #SQLite #w
<li>{ wow.  this is a really in-depth program. triggers, indexes, constraints, db info and sql all there with some swipes. zoom for tables-view looks like a life-fustration-saver. given would be more useful if could skip to a certain view(swipes-view not the data(whatever it is)) through menu or quick click..
